cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CL. 

The paper proposes a model for unsupervised feature learning using video data, which involves both computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions that the models are borrowed from the language modeling literature and adapted to the vision domain, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of generative models, which suggests that it may belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
